{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 26,
  "title": "第二十六章（輜重）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "重為巠根 清為趮君"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以君子眾日行 不離亓甾重"
    },
    {
      "text": "唯有環官 燕處則昭"
    },
    {
      "text": "若若何萬乘之王 而以身巠於天下"
    },
    {
      "text": "巠則失本 趮則失君"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人君不重則不尊，治身不重則失神，草木之花葉輕，故零落，根重故長存也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人君不靜則失威，治身不靜則身危，龍靜故能變化，虎躁故夭虧也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "輜，靜也。聖人終日行道，不離其靜與重也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "榮觀，謂宮闕。燕處，后妃所居也。超然，遠避而不處也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "奈何者，疾時主傷痛之辭。萬乘之主謂王。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "王者至尊，而以其身行輕躁乎。疾時王奢恣輕淫也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "王者輕淫則失其臣，治身輕淫則失其精。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "王者行躁疾則失其君位，治身躁疾則失其精神也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "凡物輕不能載重，小不能鎮大。不行者使行，不動者制動，是以重必為輕根，靜必為躁君也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以重為本，故不離。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不以經心也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "輕，不鎮重也，失本，為喪身也，失君，為失君位也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
